SIMPLE: karma
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Karma
<hw>Kar"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Buddhism, Hinduism)</fld> <def>One's acts considered
as fixing one's lot in the future existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theos.)</fld> <def>The doctrine of fate as the
inflexible result of cause and effect, especially the principle by which
a person is rewarded or punished in a subsequent incarnation for deeds
in the previous incarnation; the theory of inevitable
consequence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One's destiny; fate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mysticism)</fld> <def>The supposed non-physical
emanations that a person gives off, which may affect other people;
vibrations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Karmathian</ent>⟦br⟧
